response:
The base of the triangle is $BQ$ of length 12, and its height is $QC=p$. We know that the area of a triangle (\textit{base}x{\textit{height}}/2), so the area is:\end think>
\begin{align*}
&\frac{(12)(p)}{(2)} \\
&\boxed{6p}\\
\end{align*}

